the module called HypothesisTesting
    with concern: proving the Boss's theories on front-end failure

-- Hypothesis 1: Intent Greediness (as: on same line)
the behavior called greedy-intent
    with intent: this documentation swallows the keyword as: { 0 }

-- Hypothesis 2: Article Collision (variable named 'a')
the behavior called article-collision
    takes: an integer called input
    delivers: an integer
    as:
        derivation: a derives-from 1
        derivation: result derives-from a added-to input
        result

-- Hypothesis 3: Missing Braces
the behavior called brace-test
    takes: nothing
    delivers: an integer
    as: {
        1
    }

-- Hypothesis 4: Operator Identity
the behavior called operator-identity
    takes: an integer called x
    delivers: an integer
    as:
        derivation: res derives-from x opposes 1
        res
